name: Swallow fire
description:
In Mexico, it is very common to find homeless people and merchants who make a living at bus stops, traffic lights, street crossings, and who are even willing to risk their own physique in exchange for a few coins.

But among the jugglers and vendors, perhaps the most peculiar performers at Mexican traffic lights are the fire-eaters, who take large gulps of gasoline and then spit flames from their mouths.

However, there are times when the process can be complicated, and you risk receiving serious burns on your body.
